<article>
    <h1>8 new supermarke&#xAD;ts to check out</h1>
    <h2>Fill your bas&#xAD;kets with ar&#xAD;ti&#xAD;sanal pro&#xAD;duce, Ja&#xAD;panese snacks, South-east Asian goods and ve&#xAD;gan items</h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20210103/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2021-01-03"><time>2021-01-03</time></a>
        - <span>FRONT PAGE</span>
        - <span role="byline">Eu&#xAD;nice Quek&#xD;&#xA;Food Correspond&#xAD;ent eu&#xAD;niceq@sph.com.sg&#xD;&#xA;Fol&#xAD;low The Straits Times Food on Face&#xAD;book and In&#xAD;sta&#xAD;gram @strait&#xAD;stimes&#xAD;food</span>
    </section>

    <p>Gro­cery shopping – on­line or in­store – has gone from te­dious chore to plea­sur­able pas­time af­ter last year’s cir­cuit breaker pe­riod.</p>
    <p>Never have so many been so happy to see fully lined shelves of greens, meats, cans and pack­ets.</p>
    <p>More niche gourmet gro­cers and new supermarke­ts have popped up in re­cent months to feed the gro­cery hunt­ing frenzy.</p>
    <p>Many of these new of­fer­ings stand out from the usual flu­o­res­cent-lit sus­pects sell­ing the same brands.</p>
    <p>They stock themed, spe­cial­ity or ar­ti­sanal pro­duce. Their goods are sourced di­rectly from farms or sup­pli­ers, en­abling them to show­case a more cu­rated range of of­fer­ings at bet­ter prices.</p>
    <p>Ev­ery­day Ve­gan Gro­cer at The Grand­stand of­fers a wide se­lec­tion of ve­gan prod­ucts, while Asia</p>
    <p>Mart in Hougang fo­cuses on goods from South-east Asian coun­tries.</p>
    <p>Over at Scar­lett su­per­mar­ket in Chi­na­town and Gey­lang, an ex­ten­sive va­ri­ety of Chi­nese snacks and bev­er­ages – said to have some of the low­est prices in town – is stocked.</p>
    <p>And for those miss­ing Ja­pan, the 24,000 sq ft Meidi-Ya at Mil­lenia Walk of­fers two floors of so­lace, along with a din­ing sec­tion for ra­men, bento or beer, for you to fill your tummy af­ter your trol­ley.</p>
    <p>The Sun­day Times high­lights eight new week­end stomp­ing grounds for your next su­per­mar­ket sweep.</p>

